 shows a\nsharp antiferromagnetic (AFM) transition at around 14 K, and in the mixed\nvalent Pr$_{1.5}$Sr$_{0.5}$MgIrO$_6$ sample the AFM transition is shifted to a\nmuch lower temperature ($\\sim$ 6 K) due to weakening of the AFM exchange.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 Aug 2019 13:50:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-02"}
